<Content>Do NOT stay at this Hostel (not a Hotel at all) Stayed at this hotel for 3 nights, well put it this way that it is not what I expected, after reading the review on the website, I thought it was people just moaning, and because i was going Amsterdam to sight see just need somewhere to sleep ! Well I wish I didnt book it, I booked through Expedia, where I payed the full amount, so I could not change or cancel or I would have definitely left early.Arrived at the hotel, took ages to check in, had to walk so many stairs (no lift) with a big suitcase, whilst going up the stairs there was a hoover on the stair case, I nearlly fell down until my mate moved it and helped me with my luggage. Trying to find our room, there were so many things on the stairs and corriders (dirty towels/bed sheets) but we still laughed it off.Walked into the room and felt like crying, it was horrible, so small, little bunk beds, cheap flooring, opened the windows, realised we were next to a dirty cinema and opposite the red light bit. The room smelt of the class C drug.The bed sheets were so dirty, dreded to sleep there at night, however we thought it would be fine. The first night was so horrible, so loud outside, beware of the works being done in the canal, they start at 6 am! And no double glazed windows means you can hear everything ! In the morning I had red spots all over my my legs and arms, before someone wrote about bed bugs and scabbies (I did not believe it), well this is exactly what I have, after going to the pharmacy they confirmed this, I cannot believe it, I know for a fact they did not change the bed sheet for the days we were there.The breakfast in the morning was okay, the staff were okay as well, friendly and always smiling, the breakfast could do abit better, but who can complain when your whole body is itching from the night before. The only thing I can say is do not stay here no matter how cheap, go to a better hotel and pay the little bit more, its well worth it. The only positive thing about the hotel is the location and how close it is to everything !If you are staying here good luck, and take a sleeping bag or something !! 
